#load read and select the original data

df2 <- read.csv(file="//Users//lianzhihui//Desktop//model_data.csv", header=TRUE, sep=",")
df2<-df2[,c("Trilingualism","education_level","age","monthly_income","employment_status","birthplace","mother_tongue")]
df2<-drop_na(df2)
col<-c("Trilingualism","education_level","monthly_income","employment_status","birthplace","mother_tongue")
df2<-df2%>%
  mutate_at(col,funs(factor(.)))

#model multinominal

#final model

model_stepwise<-multinom(formula = Trilingualism ~ age + education_level + monthly_income + 
    employment_status + birthplace +mother_tongue, data = df2, Hess = T)
